2=Obi |date=May 2012 |title=Three-dimensional structural evolution and kinematics of the Piedemonte Llanero, Central Llanos foothills, Eastern Cordillera, Colombia |volume=39|pages=216-227|doi=10.1016/j.jsames.2012.04.012 |url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/241689024_Three-dimensional_structural_evolution_and_kinematics_of_the_Piedemonte_Llanero_Central_Llanos_foothills_Eastern_Cordillera_Colombia}} </ref>\n\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikispecies|Caryodendron orinocense}}\n{{Commons|Caryodendron orinocense}}\n\n* [https://eol.org/pages/1148517 \u00ab''Caryodendron orinocense'' H. Karst.\u00bb], Encyclopedia of Life.\n* [https://www.gbif.org/species/3055897 \u00abCaryodendron orinocense Karst.\u00bb], Global Biodiversity Information Facility.\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5753991}}\n\n[[Category:Flora of northern South America]]\n[[Category:Plants_described_in_1858]]\n[[Category:Flora of western South America]]\n[[Category:Acalyphoideae]]\n", "name_user": "CPC273", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePropagation", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caryodendron_orinocense"}
{"title_page": "Dawn Fitzpatrick", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Dawn Fitzpatrick\n| image              = Dawn Fitzpatrick headshot.jpg\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = American\n| other_names        = \n| alma_mater         = [[Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania]] <small>([[Bachelor of Science|B.S.]])</small>\n| occupation         = [[Chief investment officer|Chief Investment Officer]], [[Soros Fund Management]]\n| years_active       = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n| children           = 3\n}}\n\n'''Dawn Fitzpatrick''' is an American [[investment banker]] and financial officer based in [[New York City]]. She is known for her work as a [[hedge fund]] manager and as the [[Chief investment officer|Chief Investment Officer]] (CIO) at [[Soros Fund Management]].\n\n==Early years==\nFitzpatrick \"is a second-generation [[Irish Americans|Irish American]] with ancestors hailing from [[Kilkenny]] and [[Cork (city)|Cork]] on her father's and mother's side\", and is a native of [[New York (state)|New York]]. She holds a [[Bachelor of Science]] from the [[University of Pennsylvania]]'s [[Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania|Wharton School of Business]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://irishamerica.com/2014/09/dawn-fitzpatrick/|title=Dawn Fitzpatrick/UBS O'Connor|date=|newspaper=Irish America}}</ref> While at UPenn Fitzpatrick ran [[Track and field|track]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pennathletics.com/ViewArticle.dbml?ATCLID=52800|title=Women's Track & Field and Cross Country Letterwinners|date=June 4, 2002|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160623212450/http://www.pennathletics.com/ViewArticle.dbml?ATCLID=52800|archive-date=2016-06-23|url-status=dead|agency=Penn Athletics|df=}}</ref>  She is married with three children.<ref name=\"soros\" />\n\n==Career==\nFitzpatrick started working at [[O'Connor & Associates]] in 1992 and went on to become the global head and CIO of O'Connor within the alternative and quantitative investments area.  In August 2013, when O'Connor became a standalone business area within [[UBS|UBS Global Asset Management]], Fitzpatrick was promoted to global head and chief investment officer (CIO) at O'Connor.<ref>{{cite news |date= |title=Dawn Fitzpatrick |url=https://www.managedfunds.org/conference_speakers/dawn-fitzpatrick/ |agency=Managed Funds Association }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=November 14, 2014 |title=O'Connor Hedge Fund Scores Gains Where Prop Desks Exited |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2014-11-14/o-connor-hedge-fund-scores-gains-where-prop-desks-exited |agency=Bloomberg News }}</ref><ref name=\"bloomberg.com\">{{cite news |date=November 24, 2015 |title=UBS Names Fitzpatrick to Lead Combined Fund Unit in Shakeup |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-11-24/ubs-names-fitzpatrick-to-lead-combined-fund-business-in-shakeup |agency=Bloomberg News }}</ref>\n\nIn January 2016, Fitzpatrick became the Global Head of Equities, Multi-Asset and O'Connor at UBS Asset Management, responsible for overseeing more than $500 billion in assets.<ref name=\"bloomberg.com\"/> In January 2017, she became Head of Investments within UBS Asset Management.<ref>{{cite news |date=January 31, 2017 |title=Soros Hires New Chief Investment Officer |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/soros-hires-new-chief-investment-officer-1485909729 |newspaper=The Wall Street Journal }}</ref> She was also a member of the UBS Asset Management Executive Committee.<ref name=\"hfj\">{{cite news |date=June 18, 2015 |title=50 Leading Women In Hedge Funds 2015 |url=https://thehedgefundjournal.com/wp-content/uploads/attachments/THFJ_50_Leading_Women_In_Hedge_Funds_2015_0.pdf#page=11 |newspaper=The Hedge Fund Journal }}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, Fitzpatrick became the Chief Investment Officer of [[Soros Fund Management]].<ref name=\"soros\">{{cite news |date=April 8, 2017 |title= Men Bet She Would Fail; Now She Runs a $26 Billion Fund |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/08/business/dealbook/george-soros-dawn-fitzpatrick-american-stock-exchange.html |newspaper=The New York Times }}</ref> She currently serves on the [[Open Society Foundations]]' Economic Justice Program advisory board,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/who-we-are/programs/economic-justice-program |title=Economic Justice Program |access-date=November 3, 2019 |publisher=Open Society Foundations }}</ref> the [[Federal Reserve Bank of New York]]'s Investor Advisory Committee on Financial Markets,<ref>{{cite news |access-date=January 14, 2019 |title=Investor Advisory Committee on Financial Markets |url=https://www.newyorkfed.org/aboutthefed/ag_financial_markets.html |agency=Federal Reserve Bank of New York }}</ref> and as a non-executive Director on the [[Barclays]] board.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://home.barclays/who-we-are/structure-and-leadership/leadership/dawn-fitzpatrick/ |title=Dawn Fitzpatrick |last= |first= |date= |website= |publisher=Barclays |access-date=November 3, 2019 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=September 26, 2019 |title=Barclays Adds Prominent Investment Executives to Board |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/barclays-adds-prominent-investment-executives-to-board-11569497255 |work=The Wall Street Journal |location= |access-date= }}</ref>\n\nFitzpatrick was named one of [[Business Insider|''Business Insider''{{'s}}]] most powerful women on [[Wall Street]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.businessinsider.in/The-25-Most-Powerful-Women-On-Wall-Street/Dawn-Fitzpatrick/slideshow/21277279.cms|title=The 25 Most Powerful Women On Wall Street: Dawn Fitzpatrick|date=March 8, 2013|newspaper=Business Insider}}</ref> In 2015, ''[[American Banker]]'' put her on their list of the 25 most powerful women in finance and ''[[The Hedge Fund Journal]]'' put her on the list of 50 leading women in [[hedge fund]]s.<ref>{{cite news |date=September 22, 2015 |title=The 25 Most Powerful Women in Finance: No. 24: Dawn Fitzpatrick, UBS O'Connor |url=http://www.americanbanker.com/news/national-regional/the-25-most-powerful-women-in-finance-dawn-fitzpatrick-ubs-oconnor-1076829-1.html |newspaper=American Banker }}</ref> In 2018 and 2019, Fitzpatrick was on the ''[[Worth (magazine)|Worth]]'' Power 100, a list of \"the 100 most powerful men and women in global finance.\"<ref>{{cite news |access-date=September 17, 2019 |title=The Power 100 2019|url=https://www.worth.com/power-100-2018/#dawn-fitzpatrick |work=Worth }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |access-date=November 3, 2019 |title=The Power 100 2018 |url=https://www.worth.com/the-power-100-2019/ |work=Worth }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fitzpatrick, Dawn}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:21st-century American businesswomen]]\n[[Category:21st-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:American women business executives]]\n[[Category:UBS people]]\n[[Category:Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century businesswomen]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Dawn Fitzpatrick\n| image              = Dawn Fitzpatrick headshot.jpg\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = American\n| other_names        = \n| alma_mater         = [[Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania]] <small>([[Bachelor of Science|B.S.]])</small>\n| occupation         = [[Chief investment officer|Chief Investment Officer]], [[Soros Fund Management]]\n| years_active       = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n| children           = 3\n}}\n\n'''Dawn Fitzpatrick''' is an American [[investment banker]] and financial officer based in [[New York City]]. She is known for her work as a [[hedge fund]] manager and as the [[Chief investment officer|Chief Investment Officer]] (CIO) at [[Soros Fund Management]].\n\n==Early years==\nFitzpatrick \"is a second-generation [[Irish Americans|Irish American]] with ancestors hailing from [[Kilkenny]] and [[Cork (city)|Cork]] on her father's and mother's side\", and is a native of [[New York (state)|New York]]. She holds a [[Bachelor of Science]] from the [[University of Pennsylvania]]'s [[Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania|Wharton School of Business]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://irishamerica.com/2014/09/dawn-fitzpatrick/|title=Dawn Fitzpatrick/UBS O'Connor|date=|newspaper=Irish America}}</ref> While at UPenn Fitzpatrick ran [[Track and field|track]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pennathletics.com/ViewArticle.dbml?ATCLID=52800|title=Women's Track & Field and Cross Country Letterwinners|date=June 4, 2002|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160623212450/http://www.pennathletics.com/ViewArticle.dbml?ATCLID=52800|archive-date=2016-06-23|url-status=dead|agency=Penn Athletics|df=}}</ref>  She is married with three children.<ref name=\"soros\" />\n\n==Career==\nFitzpatrick started working at [[O'Connor & Associates]] in 1992 and went on to become the global head and CIO of O'Connor within the alternative and quantitative investments area.  In August 2013, when O'Connor became a standalone business area within [[UBS|UBS Global Asset Management]], Fitzpatrick was promoted to global head and chief investment officer (CIO) at O'Connor.<ref>{{cite news |date= |title=Dawn Fitzpatrick |url=https://www.managedfunds.org/conference_speakers/dawn-fitzpatrick/ |agency=Managed Funds Association }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=November 14, 2014 |title=O'Connor Hedge Fund Scores Gains Where Prop Desks Exited |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2014-11-14/o-connor-hedge-fund-scores-gains-where-prop-desks-exited |agency=Bloomberg News }}</ref><ref name=\"bloomberg.com\">{{cite news |date=November 24, 2015 |title=UBS Names Fitzpatrick to Lead Combined Fund Unit in Shakeup |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-11-24/ubs-names-fitzpatrick-to-lead-combined-fund-business-in-shakeup |agency=Bloomberg News }}</ref>\n\nIn January 2016, Fitzpatrick became the Global Head of Equities, Multi-Asset and O'Connor at UBS Asset Management, responsible for overseeing more than $500 billion in assets.<ref name=\"bloomberg.com\"/> In January 2017, she became Head of Investments within UBS Asset Management.<ref>{{cite news |date=January 31, 2017 |title=Soros Hires New Chief Investment Officer |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/soros-hires-new-chief-investment-officer-1485909729 |newspaper=The Wall Street Journal }}</ref> She was also a member of the UBS Asset Management Executive Committee.<ref name=\"hfj\">{{cite news |date=June 18, 2015 |title=50 Leading Women In Hedge Funds 2015 |url=https://thehedgefundjournal.com/wp-content/uploads/attachments/THFJ_50_Leading_Women_In_Hedge_Funds_2015_0.pdf#page=11 |newspaper=The Hedge Fund Journal }}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, Fitzpatrick became the Chief Investment Officer of [[Soros Fund Management]].<ref name=\"soros\">{{cite news |date=April 8, 2017 |title= Men Bet She Would Fail; Now She Runs a $26 Billion Fund |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/08/business/dealbook/george-soros-dawn-fitzpatrick-american-stock-exchange.html |newspaper=The New York Times }}</ref> She currently serves on the [[Open Society Foundations]]' Economic Justice Program advisory board,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/who-we-are/programs/economic-justice-program |title=Economic Justice Program |access-date=November 3, 2019 |publisher=Open Society Foundations }}</ref> the [[Federal Reserve Bank of New York]]'s Investor Advisory Committee on Financial Markets,<ref>{{cite news |access-date=January 14, 2019 |title=Investor Advisory Committee on Financial Markets |url=https://www.newyorkfed.org/aboutthefed/ag_financial_markets.html |agency=Federal Reserve Bank of New York }}</ref> and as a non-executive Director on the [[Barclays]] board.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://home.barclays/who-we-are/structure-and-leadership/leadership/dawn-fitzpatrick/ |title=Dawn Fitzpatrick |last= |first= |date= |website= |publisher=Barclays |access-date=November 3, 2019 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=September 26, 2019 |title=Barclays Adds Prominent Investment Executives to Board |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/barclays-adds-prominent-investment-executives-to-board-11569497255 |work=The Wall Street Journal |location= |access-date= }}</ref>\n\nFitzpatrick was named one of [[Business Insider|''Business Insider''{{'s}}]] most powerful women on [[Wall Street]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.businessinsider.in/The-25-Most-Powerful-Women-On-Wall-Street/Dawn-Fitzpatrick/slideshow/21277279.cms|title=The 25 Most Powerful Women On Wall Street: Dawn Fitzpatrick|date=March 8, 2013|newspaper=Business Insider}}</ref> In 2015, ''[[American Banker]]'' put her on their list of the 25 most powerful women in finance and ''[[The Hedge Fund Journal]]'' put her on the list of 50 leading women in [[hedge fund]]s.<ref>{{cite news |date=September 22, 2015 |title=The 25 Most Powerful Women in Finance: No. 24: Dawn Fitzpatrick, UBS O'Connor |url=http://www.americanbanker.com/news/national-regional/the-25-most-powerful-women-in-finance-dawn-fitzpatrick-ubs-oconnor-1076829-1.html |newspaper=American Banker }}</ref> In 2018 and 2019, Fitzpatrick was on the ''[[Worth (magazine)|Worth]]'' Power 100, a list of \"the 100 most powerful men and women in global finance.\"<ref>{{cite news |access-date=September 17, 2019 |title=The Power 100 2019|url=https://www.worth.com/power-100-2018/#dawn-fitzpatrick |work=Worth }}</ref><ref>